source: A configurable widget that shows a select2.

Define a width for the select2 field. It can be either 'element', 'computedstyle', 'style', 'resolve' or any possible CSS unit. E.g. 500px, 50%, 200em. See the select2 documentation for further explanations.

Define a width for the select2 field. It can be either 'element', 'computedstyle', 'style', 'resolve' or any possible CSS value. E.g. 500px, 50%, 200em. See the select2 documentation for further explanations.
Indicates the status of referenced entities.
Make sure that the select2 lib is placed in the library folder. You can download the release of your choice from GitHub.
Makes entity reference fields more user-friendly using Select2.
Options will be lazy loaded. This is recommended for lists with a lot of values.
Select the method used to collect autocomplete suggestions. Note that Contains can cause performance issues on sites with thousands of entities.
The number of suggestions that will be listed. Use 0 to remove the limit.
